<subSubSection box="[151,1033,1719,1744]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1719,2032]" box="[151,1033,1719,1744]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1719,1744]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is a contraction of the name of the 
<typeStatus box="[887,935,1720,1744]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1719,2032]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1755,1780]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</emphasis>
Although 
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" box="[440,578,1755,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baviaans" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[440,578,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. baviaans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[587,679,1755,1780]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[587,679,1755,1780]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is known from the male only and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" box="[1085,1226,1755,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilineata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1085,1226,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. trilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1236,1328,1755,1780]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1236,1328,1755,1780]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from the female only, and both were collected in the same pitfall traps, we believe that they are distinctive species based on their considerable size differences (
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" box="[555,695,1827,1852]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilineata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[555,695,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. trilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[704,795,1827,1852]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[704,795,1827,1852]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
almost double the body length of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" box="[1190,1327,1827,1852]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baviaans" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1190,1327,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. baviaans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1335,1427,1827,1852]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1335,1427,1827,1852]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) and the very different abdominal markings (spotted in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" box="[776,913,1863,1888]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baviaans" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[776,913,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. baviaans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[922,1013,1863,1888]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[922,1013,1863,1888]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and with narrow lateral stripes in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilineata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. trilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[265,357,1899,1924]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[265,357,1899,1924]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), particularly since all other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitt" authorityYear="1916" box="[817,954,1899,1924]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[817,954,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Drassodella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have similar colouration and markings in both sexes (
<figureCitation box="[283,425,1935,1960]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–110" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1792,1814]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,195,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[160,1427,195,1770]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 93–110. Dorsal habitus photographs of Drassodella species in the melana species group: 93, 94 female and male of D. flava sp. nov.; 95, 96 female and male of D. guttata sp. nov.; 97 female of D. lotzi sp. nov.; 98 female of D. maculata sp. nov.; 99, 100 female and male of D. melana Tucker, 1923; 101, 102 female and male of D. montana sp. nov.; 103, 104 female and male of D. tenebrosa Lawrence, 1938; 105, 106 female and male of D. tolkieni sp. nov.; 107, 108 female and male of D. transversa sp. nov.; 109, 110 female and male of D. venda sp. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2643746/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figs 93–110</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[437,539,1935,1960]" captionStart="FIGURES 157–171" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1272,1294]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,193,1251]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[161,1426,193,1251]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 157–171. Dorsal habitus photographs of Drassodella species in the salisburyi species group: 157, 158 female and male of D. amatola sp. nov.; 159, 160 female and male of D. aurostriata sp. nov.; 161 male of D. baviaans sp. nov.; 162 female of D. purcelli Tucker, 1923; 163, 164 female and male of D. quinquelabecula Tucker, 1923; 165, 166 female and male of D. salisburyi Hewitt, 1916; 167, 168 female and male of D. septemmaculata (Strand, 1909); 169 female of D. trilineata sp. nov.; 170, 171 female and male of D. vasivulva Tucker, 1923. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2643776/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">157–171</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1719,2032]" lastBlockId="43.[151,1437,151,1005]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1971,1996]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" box="[432,566,1971,1996]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baviaans" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[432,566,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. baviaans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[572,662,1971,1996]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[572,662,1971,1996]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mbo &amp; Haddad, 2019" authorityName="Mbo &amp; Haddad" authorityYear="2019" box="[976,1102,1971,1996]" class="Arachnida" family="Gallieniellidae" genus="Drassodella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amatola" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[976,1102,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">D. amatola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1108,1197,1971,1996]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1108,1197,1971,1996]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but can be separated by the larger median apophysis, the pointed embolus tip, and the lack of a prolateral tegular protrusion (compare 
<figureCitation box="[151,248,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 180–183" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1905,1927]" captionTargetBox="[167,1422,1059,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[161,1426,1052,1884]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 180–183. Genitalic morphology of Drassodella baviaans sp. nov. (180, 181) and D. purcelli Tucker, 1923 (182, 183): 180 male palp, ventral view; 181 same, retrolateral view; 182 female epigyne, ventral view; 183 same, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.25mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2643786/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs 180</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[302,348,152,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 172–175" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1395,1417]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,622,1376]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[161,1426,611,1382]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 172–175. Genitalic morphology of Drassodella amatola sp. nov.: 172 female epigyne, ventral view; 173 same, dorsal view; 174 male palp, ventral view; 175 same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.25mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2643780/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">174</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,927,188,213]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus box="[428,540,188,213]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Holotype</typeStatus>
, Baviaanskloof, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dippenaar-Schoeman, A. S. &amp; Haddad, C. R. &amp; Foord, S. &amp; Lyle, R. &amp; Lotz, L. &amp; Helberg, L. &amp; Mathebula, S. &amp; Van den Berg, A. &amp; Marais, P. &amp; Van den Berg, M. A. &amp; Van Niekerk, E. &amp; Jocque, R." box="[736,863,188,213]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 1145" refId="ref44308" refString="Dippenaar-Schoeman, A. S., Haddad, C. R., Foord, S., Lyle, R., Lotz, L., Helberg, L., Mathebula, S., Van den Berg, A., Marais, P., Van den Berg, M. A., Van Niekerk, E. &amp; Jocque, R. (2010) First atlas of the spiders of South Africa (Arachnida: Araneae). South African National Survey of Arachnida technical report 2010, Version 1, 1 - 1145." type="book chapter" year="2010">NCA 2010</bibRefCitation>
/241).
</emphasis>
Measurements: CL 2.10, CW 1.24, AL 2.18, AW 1.16, TL 4.60 (3.88–4.60), FL 0.14, SL 1.14, SW 0.96, 
<collectingCountry box="[850,889,224,248]" name="Switzerland" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">CH</collectingCountry>
0.12, AME-AME 0.06, AME-ALE 0.02, ALE- ALE 0.20, PME-PME 0.09, PME-PLE 0.13, PLE-PLE 0.40, PERW 0.53, MOQAW 0.17, MOQPW 0.21, MOQL 0.25.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Length of leg segments: I 1.54 + 0.76 + 1.28 + 1.22 + 1.02 = 5.82, II 1.34 + 0.64 + 1.00 + 1.04 + 0.76 = 4.78, III 1.04 + 0.58 + 0.76 + 0.88 + 0.62 = 3.88, IV 1.84 + 0.76 + 1.40 + 1.92 + 0.82 = 6.74.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
General appearance as in 
<figureCitation box="[512,614,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 157–171" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1272,1294]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,193,1251]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[161,1426,193,1251]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 157–171. Dorsal habitus photographs of Drassodella species in the salisburyi species group: 157, 158 female and male of D. amatola sp. nov.; 159, 160 female and male of D. aurostriata sp. nov.; 161 male of D. baviaans sp. nov.; 162 female of D. purcelli Tucker, 1923; 163, 164 female and male of D. quinquelabecula Tucker, 1923; 165, 166 female and male of D. salisburyi Hewitt, 1916; 167, 168 female and male of D. septemmaculata (Strand, 1909); 169 female of D. trilineata sp. nov.; 170, 171 female and male of D. vasivulva Tucker, 1923. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2643776/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 161</figureCitation>
. Carapace red-brown; white feathery setae forming upsilon marking, diverging behind fovea. Clypeus height equal to 1.25 AME diameter; AME smaller than ALE; AME separated by distance equal to 0.75 their diameter, AME separated from ALE by distance equal to 0.25 AME diameter; PME smaller than PLE; PME separated by distance equal to 1.26 their diameter, PME separated from PLE by distance equal to 1.63 PME diameter. Chelicerae dark-brown; promargin with three teeth, median tooth largest, distal tooth smallest; median tooth closer to proximal tooth; retromargin with two subequal widely space teeth. Endites orange, darker around margins. Labium orange, slightly longer than wide. Sternum brown. Legs with orange proximal segments, distal segments yellow. Leg spination: femora: I do 1 rl 1, II do 1 rl 1, III pl 2 do 2 rl 1, IV pl 1 do 2 rl 1; patellae: spineless; tibiae: I, II &amp; III spineless, IV do 2 rl 3; metatarsi: I, II &amp; III spineless, III rl 4 plv 2; palpal spination: femora do 2 rl 1 plv 2; patellae do 2 rl 3 plv 1; tibiae do 6 rl 2 plv 1; tarsi spineless. Abdomen brown; dorsal scutum extending two-thirds abdomen length; three pairs of dorsolateral spots of white feathery setae, one white spot above spinnerets; lateral sclerites above booklungs oval; venter grey, with large orange markings. Spinnerets pale. Palp yellow-brown; RTA moderately long, not obscured in ventral view by retrolateral heel of cymbium but positioned retrolateral of cymbium; in retrolateral view triangular, slightly curved dorsally, with broad base and sharp tip; cymbium narrow, 1.97 times longer than wide, narrowed to rounded point distally; embolus originating from distal prolateral mound, transverse and directed retrolaterally, with sharp needle-like tip; median apophysis large, hook-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[587,673,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–92" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1460,1482]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,190,1448]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[157,1429,190,1448]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 78–92. Male palps of Drassodella species of the D. melana species group (78–85) and D. salisburyi species group (86–92) in ventral view: 78 D. flava sp. nov.; 79 D. guttata sp. nov.; 80 D. melana Tucker, 1923; 81 D. montana sp. nov.; 82 D. tenebrosa Lawrence, 1923; 83 D. tolkieni sp. nov.; 84 D. transversa sp. nov.; 85 D. venda sp. nov.; 86 D. amatola sp. nov.; 87 D. aurostriata sp. nov.; 88 D. baviaans sp. nov.; 89 D. quinquelabecula Tucker, 1923; 90 D. salisburyi Hewitt, 1916; 91 D. septemmaculata (Strand, 1909); 92 D. vasivulva Tucker, 1923. Abbreviations as follows: DP—dorsal embolic prong; EMembolus; MA—median apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; VP—ventral embolic prong. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2643744/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs 88</figureCitation>
